f this zone.<ref name=GCivil/> Unlike tourism in central Portugal, the region is sought for its unspoiled nature and rural tourism; its agrarian lifestyle, although an important part of its enchantment, supports the local population, primarily in cattle-raising, dairy production and cultivation of rye and wheat.<ref name=GCivil/>\n\nIn the urban areas, particularly the municipal seats, the primary economic activities predominate, including the public-sector institutions, commerce and industry.<ref name=GCivil/>\n\nThe difficulty in communication and interconnection between markets was always a problem in this region, resulting in few investments and economic development.<ref name=GCivil/> Tourism still remains the sector of the economy that has potential to improve development, and fix a transient population.<ref name=GCivil/>\n\n==Culture==\n[[File:Casa de Pedra.jpg|thumb|235px|left|A stone home from the 17th century in the municipality of Mogadouro]] \n[[Leonese language]] was widely spoken in the territory, but today, there are few who speak the language (which is primarily concentrated in the communities near Rio de Onor, Guadramil and along the northeast to southeast frontier with Spain). [[Mirandese language|Mirandese]], a local variant, is commonly observed in the regions of the District, particularly around [[Miranda do Douro Municipality|Miranda do Douro]], and has resulted in its official recognition by the Portuguese Parliament.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Rio de Fornos]], a village in the district of Bragan\u00e7a\n\n{{Municipalities of Bragan\u00e7a}}\n{{Districts of Portugal}}\n\n==References==\n;Notes\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n* {{citation|last=Abrunhosa|first=Vasco|year=2002|publisher=Governo Civil de Bragan\u00e7a|location=Bragan\u00e7a, Portugal|url=http://gcivilbraganca.cidadevirtual.pt|date=5 October 2004|language=Portuguese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060618210613/http://gcivilbraganca.cidadevirtual.pt/|archivedate=18 June 2006}}\n* {{citation|url=http://bibliotecadigital.ipb.pt/bitstream/10198/1023/1/n_15.pdf|title=Quantitative Analysis of Financial Indicators for Municipalities: Comparison of Portugal (Bragan\u00e7a District) and Slovenia|author=Sreko Devjak|year=2007|publisher=Comparative International Governmental Accounting Research/Biennial CIGAR Conference|location=Coimbra, Portugal|accessdate=27 May 2001|display-authors=etal}}\n* {{cite book|first=Lu\u00eds|last=Silveira|title=Territ\u00f3rio e Poder. Nas Origens do Estado Contempor\u00e2neo em Portugal|trans-title=Territory and Power. At the Origins of Modern State in Portugal|publisher=Patrim\u00f3nia|location=, Cascais, Portugal|year=1997|language=Portuguese}}\n* {{citation|title=A seminar game to analyze regional governance options for Portugal|first=James P.|last=Kahan|editor=Luso-American Development Foundation|publisher=RAND|location=Washington D.C., United States|year=1999|accessdate=27 May 2011|url=https://books.google.com/?id=oN70bqwyegQC&pg=PA1&dq=distritos+portugal#v=onepage&q=districts&f=false|isbn=9780833026965}}\n* {{citation|url=http://www.gov-civil-braga.pt/admin/upload%5CInforma%C3%A7%C3%B5es%20Uteis%5CDistritos%20-%20Governadores%20Civis/Distritos%20-%20Governadores%20Civis%20-%20Uma%20abordagem,%20uma%20reflexa%20EM%20TEMPO.pdf|title=Distritos - Governadores Civis. Uma Abordagem, Uma Reflex\u00e3o: Em Tempo|accessdate=27 May 2011|year=2002|location=Braga, Portugal|publisher=Governo Civil de Braga|language=Portuguese}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/vitor107/collections/72157594587125197/ Photos from Bragan\u00e7a (district)]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Braganca (District)}}\n<!--Categories-->\n[[Category:Districts of Portugal]]\n[[Category:Bragan\u00e7a District| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|District of Portugal}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Bragan\u00e7a\n| native_name             = \